    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I have already done that @vvo. For example at category page (/women-clothes) if I click on a sub category (dresses) in hierarchicalMenu widget I want pathname to be /dresses.\n\nMy current configuration: \n\n``` javascript\nvar locationPath = window.location.pathname;\nvar searchParameters = {\n    hierarchicalFacetsRefinements : {category: ['Women > Clothes']}\n}\nvar defaultParams = {\n    appId: 'XXXXXX',\n    apiKey: 'XXXXXX',\n    indexName: 'XXXXXX',\n    searchParameters: searchParameters,\n    urlSync:{\n        useHash: false,\n        trackedParameters:['query','page','facetsRefinements','disjunctiveFacetsRefinements','numericRefinements']\n    }\n}\nvar search = instantsearch(defaultParams);\nvar firstTime = true;\nsearch.on('render', function() {\n    $('#categories a').click(function(){\n        locationPath =  '/'+$(this).data('slug');\n    });\n    if(!firstTime){\n        ga('set', 'page', locationPath);\n        ga('send', 'pageview');\n    }\n    firstTime = false;\n});\n```\n\nThen I downloaded instantsearch.js and edited that line;\n\n``` javascript\nfunction getFullURL(relative) {\n    //return getLocationOrigin() + window.location.pathname + relative;\n    return getLocationOrigin() + locationPath + relative;\n}\n```\n\nSo I will need to check new versions of instantsearch.js, download again and update :confounded: \n\nBut such a solution would be great:\n\n``` javascript\nvar defaultParams = {\n    appId: 'XXXXXX',\n    apiKey: 'XXXXXX',\n    indexName: 'XXXXXX',\n    locationPath: window.location.pathname,\n    searchParameters: searchParameters,\n    urlSync:{\n        useHash: false,\n        trackedParameters:['query','page','facetsRefinements','disjunctiveFacetsRefinements','numericRefinements']\n    }\n}\nvar search = instantsearch(defaultParams);\nsearch.on('render', function() {\n    $('#categories a').click(function(){\n        search.helper.setLocationPath('/'+$(this).data('slug'));\n    });\n}\n```\n",
